### Constructor
--> is a special method in java that is automatically created whem Object is created.
e.g:- in a class student , constructor might initialize fields like name, age and grade when a new Object is created
 *** Fundamental concept of constructor.
- constructor have must be same name as the class name.
- it has no return type(not even void).
- It is called automatically callend when object is created.

** there are two types of constructor
1. Default Constructor(no parameter)
2. Parameterized Constructor(takes input values)

*** Constructor code 
   class Student {
      int age;
      String name;

      Student(int a, String b)
      {
         age = a;
         name = b;
      }
      void display()
        {
          System.out.println(age);
          System.out.println(name);
        }
  Public class Main {
     Public static void main(sting[] args)
        {
          Student s1 = new Strudent(1, "saurav");
          s1.display();
        }
 }
---------------code of constructor----------------------

### SHADOW PROBLEM

     public class Student {
	int roll;
	String name;
	double per;
	
	Student(int roll, String name, double per)
	{
		roll = roll;  // this will create a shadow problem.
		name = name;
		per = per;
	}
	void disp()
	{
		System.out.println(roll);
		System.out.println(name);
		System.out.println(per);
	}
}
-----Main method------
public class Main {
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		Student s1 = new Student(12,"Saurav", 89.9);
		s1.disp();
	}
}
Note:-  Local variables names and instances variables names they are the same there is the name class is occur this problem is called shadowing problem
------OverCome of Shadow Problem we can use this keyword.-------

     public class Student {
	int roll;
	String name;
	double per;
	
	Student(int roll, String name, double per)
	{
		this.roll = roll;  // this will create a shadow problem.
		this.name = name;
		this.per = per;
	}
	void disp()
	{
		System.out.println(roll);
		System.out.println(name);
		System.out.println(per);
	}
}
-----Main method------
public class Main {
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		Student s1 = new Student(12,"Saurav", 89.9);
		s1.disp();
	}
}







